The Lagos State Government has said it will give one million Information and Communication Technology devices to students to enable them to compete with their counterparts in other parts of the world. The government stated that so far, 33,000 devices had been given to students in public schools across the state. Speaking at the 2021 STEAM UP Lagos Convention, the Commissioner for Budget and Economic Planning, Mr Sam Egube, said Lagos would continue to prioritise technological development and innovations in its budget. He added that 15,000 devices had been given to teachers to increase their capacity and enable them to train the students. “Each of the devices has been configured to assist the government to monitor teachers’ efficiency, especially their resumption and teaching activities at school. About N161bn has been set aside for human capital development in the 2021 budget,”Egube said. The Senior Special Assistant to Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu on Education, Ms Adetola Salau, said Science, Technology, Engineering, Art and Mathematics represented the holistic and trans-disciplinary approach to subject matter delivery, taking into account the interrelatedness of concepts encountered in personal lives and immediate environment with a view to proffering long-term affordable and sustainable solutions to these challenges. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com